<P>THE AMERICAN PRECEPTOR; BEING A NEW SELECTION OF LESSONS FOR READING AND SPEAKING. DESIGNED FOR THE USE OF SCHOOLS.</P>
<P>BY CALEB BINGHAM, A. M. Author of the Young Lady's Accidence, and Child's Companion.</P>
<Q>"TRAIN UP A CHILD IN THE WAY HE SHOULD GO."</Q>
<P>Publi&s;hed according to Act of Congre&s;s.</P>
<P>BOSTON: PRINTED BY MANNING AND LORING, FOR THE <HI>AUTHOR,</HI> AND FOR <HI>S. HALL,</HI> NO. 53, CORNHILL.&mdash;1794.</P>
